{"title_page": "Sunday Best (Surfaces song)", "text_new": "{{Infobox song\n| name       = Sunday Best\n| type       = single\n| artist     = Surfaces\n| album      = Where the Light Is\n| published  = January 8, 2019\n| released   = July 11, 2019 {{small|(music video)}}<br>March 2020 {{small|(airplay)}}\n| genre      =\n| length     = 2:39\n| label      = {{hlist|TenThousand Projects|[[Caroline Records|Caroline]]}}\n| writer     = {{hlist|Forrest Frank|Colin Padalecki}}\n| producer   = {{hlist|Forrest Frank|Colin Padalecki}}\n| prev_title = Shine on Top\n| prev_year  = 2018\n| next_title = Palm Trees\n| next_year  = 2019\n| misc       = {{external music video|type=single|{{YouTube|83KqwEEGw4|\"Sunday Best\"}}}}\n}}\n\"'''Sunday Best'''\" is a song by American [[electro-pop]] duo Surfaces, composed of Forrest Frank and Colin Padalecki. The song was released by TenThousand Projects and [[Caroline Records]] on the duo's second album ''Where the Light Is'' on January 8, 2019. The song's music video was released on July 11, 2019.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.broadwayworld.com/bwwmusic/article/Surfaces-Shares-New-Music-Video-For-SUNDAY-BEST-20190711|title=Surfaces Shares New Music Video For SUNDAY BEST|date=July 11, 2019|website=[[BroadwayWorld]]|access-date=March 15, 2020}}</ref> The song is believed to have gained popularity in late February 2020 on the online-video sharing platform [[TikTok]],<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.billboard.com/articles/business/branding/8551350/flighthouse-republic-records-partner-tiktok-series-certified-superfan|title=Flighthouse and Republic Records Partner on New TikTok Series 'Certified Superfan'|last=Eggertsen|first=Chris|date=February 19, 2020|website=[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]]|url-status=live|access-date=March 15, 2020}}</ref> before it was released for radio airplay in early March 2020.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200302133607/https://www.allaccess.com/top40-mainstream/future-releases|title=Top 40/M Future Releases|date=March 3, 2020|website=[[All Access]]|url-status=live|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200302133607/https://www.allaccess.com/top40-mainstream/future-releases|archive-date=March 2, 2020|access-date=March 15, 2020}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.top-charts.com/s/sunday-best-surfaces|title=Sunday Best by Surfaces|website=Top-Charts.com|access-date=March 15, 2020}}</ref> The song peaked in the Top 40 in Australia, Canada, Norway, Ireland, New Zealand and the United KingdomFeeling good, like I should\nWent and took a walk around the neighborhood\nFeeling blessed, never stressed\nGot that sunshine on my Sunday best\nEvery day can be a better day despite the challenge\nAll you gotta do is leave it better than you found it\nIt's gonna get difficult to stand but hold your balance\nI just say whatever 'cause there is no way around it 'cause\nEveryone falls down sometimes\nBut you just gotta know it'll all be fine\nIt's ok, uh-huh\nIt's ok, it's ok\nFeeling good, like I should\nWent and took a walk around the neighborhood\nFeeling blessed, never stressed\nGot that sunshine on my Sunday best\nSomedays you wake up and nothing works you feel surrounded\nGotta give your feet some gravity to get you grounded\nKeep good things inside your ears just like the waves and sound did\nAnd just say whatever cause there is no way around it\nEveryone falls down sometimes\nBut you just gotta know it'll all be fine\nIt's ok, uh-huh\nIt's ok, it's ok\nFeeling good, like I should\nWent and took a walk around the neighborhood\nFeeling blessed, never stressed\nGot that sunshine on my Sunday best\nFeeling good, like I should\nWent and took a walk around the neighborhood\nFeeling blessed, never stressed\nGot that sunshine on my Sunday best \n\n== Live performances ==\nSurfaces made their late-night television debut when they performed the song on ''[[Late Night with Seth Meyers]]'' on March 2, 2020.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://headlineplanet.com/home/2020/03/03/surfaces-perform-on-late-night-with-seth-meyers-first-look/|title=Surfaces Perform \"Sunday Best\" On \"Late Night With Seth Meyers\"|last=Cantor|first=Brian|date=March 3, 2020|website=Headline Planet|access-date=March 15, 2020}}</ref>\n\n== Charts ==\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable plainrowheaders\" style=\"text-align:center\"\n|-\n! scope=\"col\"| Chart (2020)\n! scope=\"col\"| Peak<br />position\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| Australia ([[ARIA Charts|ARIA]])<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.ariacharts.com.au/charts/singles-chart|title=ARIA Australian Top 50 Singles|publisher=[[Australian Recording Industry Association]]|date=March 30, 2020|accessdate=March 28, 2020}}</ref>\n| 12\n|-\n{{single chart|Austria|70|artist=Surfaces|song=Sunday Best|rowheader=true|accessdate=March 26, 2020}}\n|-\n{{single chart|Flanders|28|artist=Surfaces|song=Sunday Best|rowheader=true|accessdate=March 28, 2020}}\n|-\n{{single chart|Wallonia Tip|3|artist=Surfaces|song=Sunday Best|rowheader=true|accessdate=March 28, 2020}}\n|-\n{{single chart|Canada|8|artist=Surfaces|rowheader=true|accessdate=March 31, 2020}}\n|-\n{{single chart|Czechdigital|12|year=2020|week=12|rowheader=true|accessdate=March 24, 2020}}\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| Denmark ([[Tracklisten]])<ref>{{cite web|url=http://hitlisten.nu/default.asp?w=11&y=2020&list=t40|title=Track Top-40 Uge 11, 2020|publisher=[[Hitlisten]]|accessdate=March 25, 2020}}</ref>\n| 30\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| Estonia (''[[Eesti Ekspress]]'')<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://ekspress.delfi.ee/areen/eesti-tipp-40-muusikas-uku-suviste-porutas-korgustesse-aga-koige-popim-lugu-eesti-laulu-finaalist-on-hoopis?id=89175431|title=EESTI TIPP-40 MUUSIKAS: Uku Suviste p\u00f5rutas k\u00f5rgustesse, aga k\u00f5ige popim lugu Eesti Laulu finaalist on hoopis...|website=[[Eesti Ekspress]]|language=Estonian|access-date=March 16, 2020}}</ref>\n| 31\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| France ([[Syndicat National de l'\u00c9dition Phonographique|SNEP]])<ref>{{cite web|url=http://snepmusique.com/les-tops/le-top-de-la-