tle=SSI updates sub sim's graphics\n  |url=http://edition.cnn.com/TECH/computing/9910/12/silent.hunter2.idg/index.html\n  |accessdate=22 January 2020\n  |ref=harv\n}}\n{{Refend}}\n\n{{s-start}}\n{{s-mil}}\n{{s-bef | before = ''Kapit\u00e4n zur See'' [[Otto Kretschmer]]}}\n{{s-ttl | title = commander of the amphibious forces | years = 1 January 1962 \u2013 30 September 1963 }}\n{{s-aft | after = ''Kapit\u00e4n zur See'' [[Adolf Piening]]}}\n{{s-bef | before = ''Konteradmiral'' [[Karl Hetz]]}}\n{{s-ttl | title = [[Deputy Inspector of the Navy]] | years = 1 October 1966 \u2013 30 September 1969 }}\n{{s-aft | after = ''Konteradmiral'' [[Heinz K\u00fchnle]]}}\n{{s-end}}\n\n{{Authority control}}\n{{Subject bar\n| portal1=Biography\n| portal2=Military of Germany\n| portal3=World War II\n| commons=y\n}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Topp, Erich}}\n[[Category:1914 births]]\n[[Category:2005 deaths]]\n[[Category:U-boat commanders (Kriegsmarine)]]\n[[Category:Nazi Party members]]\n[[Category:Recipients of the Knight's Cross of the Iron Cross with Oak Leaves and Swords]]\n[[Category:Commanders Crosses of the Order of Merit of the Federal Republic of Germany]]\n[[Category:Bundesmarine admirals]]\n[[Category:People from Hanover]]\n[[Category:People from the Province of Hanover]]\n[[Category:Reichsmarine personnel]]\n[[Category:Burials at sea]]\n[[Category:Counter admirals of the German Navy]]\n[[Category:20th-century German architects]]\n[[Category:University of Hanover alumni]]\n", "name_user": "WereSpielChequers", "label": "safe", "comment": "typo", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Erich_Topp"}
{"title_page": "Nipun Akter", "text_new": "{{Infobox person\n| name = Nipun Akter\n| image =Nipun Akter (cropped).jpg\n| caption = \n| native_name = \u09a8\u09be\u09b8\u09b0\u09bf\u09a8 \u0986\u0995\u09cd\u09a4\u09be\u09b0 \u09a8\u09bf\u09aa\u09c1\u09a3\n| native_name_lang = bn\n| birth_name = Nasrin Akter Nipun\n| birth_date = {{Birth date and age|1984|6|9|mf=yes}}\n| birth_place = [[Comilla]], Bangladesh\n| nationality = Bangladeshi\n| occupation = Actress, model\n| years active = 2006 \u2013 present\n| notable_works = [[Pitar Ason]], [[Boss Number One]]\n| height = {{height|ft=5|in=5}}\n| spouse = \n| children = Tanisha<ref>{{Cite news |script-title=bn:\u09b2\u09a8\u09cd\u09a1\u09a8\u09c7 \u09ae\u09c7\u09af\u09bc\u09c7\u09b0 \u09b8\u0999\u09cd\u0997\u09c7 \u09a8\u09bf\u09aa\u09c1\u09a3 |url=http://www.banglanews24.com/beta/fullnews/bn/320497.html |work=banglanews24.com |language=bn |access-date=2 February 2015}}</ref>\n| awards = [[National Film Awards (Bangladesh)|National Film Awards]]<br>DCRA Award<br>BABISAS Award\n| website = {{url|http://actressnipun.com}}\n}}\n\n'''Nasrin Akter Nipun''' (known as '''Nipun Akter''') is a Bangladeshi film actress. She has won the National Film Award twice. Nipun entered into the film industry in 2006.\n\n== Early life and education ==\nAfter completion of her intermediate examination, Nipun Akter went to Russia in 1999 for higher studies. She completed her Engineering graduation in Computer Science from Moscow University.<ref name=\"bbc\"/> Then she moved to [[Los Angeles]], United States.<ref name=\"bbc\">{{Cite news |script-title=bn:\u09aa\u09cd\u09b0\u09ac\u09be\u09b8 \u099c\u09c0\u09ac\u09a8 \u09ab\u09c7\u09b2\u09c7 \u09b0\u09c7\u0996\u09c7 \u09ac\u09be\u0982\u09b2\u09be\u09a6\u09c7\u09b6\u09c7\u09b0 \u09b8\u09bf\u09a8\u09c7\u09ae\u09be \u099c\u0997\u09a4\u09c7 \u09a8\u09bf\u09aa\u09c1\u09a3 \u0986\u0995\u09cd\u09a4\u09be\u09b0 |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/bengali/multimedia/2014/09/140909_sm_nipun_akter_bangladeshi_filmactress_interview |work=[[BBC Bangla]] |date=9 September 2014 |language=bn |access-date=2 February 2015}}</ref>\n\n==Acting career==\nNipun Said \"I left the country after completion of intermediate in 1999. I stayed in Moscow up to 2004 for higher studies. In the meantime, I got married and went to the United States for a living. I had a job in a pharmacy there. Life was good enough. I came back to Bangladesh in 2006 for a short visit. I got offers for acting in the film at that time suddenly. There is no one in my family who ever performed in films. So I came to act here out of curiosity. But the interesting fact is that the very first movie in which I acted has yet to be released! My first released movie is \u2018Pitar ashon\u2019.\"\n\nAfter being successful in Dhaka film industry, Film Actress Nipun has also acted in Bangla film of Kolkata. Soon she will be seen in the Tollywood film for the first time. Star Bangladeshi actor Ferdous and famous west Bengal star of the time Proshenjit has acted with her in the movie named \u2018Porichoy\u2019.\n\nBangladeshi Film Actress Nipun said in this regard, \"Actor [[Ferdous Ahmed]] played a major role to take my opportunity to act in the movie. It is he who discussed with the director Rupali Chatterjee and producer Shomu Gawal for giving me an opportunity. It is undoubtedly one of the greatest chances of my life.\" \"I was afraid hearing that I have to work with Bumbada. But when he came to me and introduced himself, I felt relieved.\"In recent times, Nipun performed in some of the commercially successful movies. In 2017, Nipun has been elected as an active member of [[Bangladesh Film Development Corporation]].<ref>{{Cite news |url=https://www.priyo.com/articles/mousumi-s-chair-is-elegant-in-the-chair-20171011 |script-title=bn:\u09ae\u09cc\u09b8\u09c1\u09ae\u09c0\u09b0 \u09b8\u09cd\u09a5\u09b2\u09be\u09ad\u09bf\u09b7\u09bf\u0995\u09cd\u09a4 \u09b9\u09b2\u09c7\u09a8 \u09a8\u09bf\u09aa\u09c1\u09a3 |work=Priyo.com |access-date=2017-10-12}}</ref>\n\n==Awards==\nBangladeshi Film Actress Nipun has so far grabbed two National Film Awards. First of all, she received the national award for the movie \u2018Shajghor\u2019 and afterward in 2009 she received a national award for acting in the movie \u2018Chader moto bou\u2019. Nipun also received other awards, including the BABISAS Award, DCRA Award, New face of the year 2006 Award and Best performer 2007 Award.\n\n==Filmography==\n\n===Films===\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|-\n! Year\n! Film\n! Director\n! Co-star\n! Role\n! Notes\n|-\n| rowspan=2 | 2006|| ''Rotnogarva Ma'' ||  || Manna || || Unreleased\n|-\n|''[[Pitar Ason]]''\n|[[Pitar Ason|FI Manik]]\n|[[Pitar Ason|Shakib Khan]]\n|[[Pitar Ason|Raika]]\n|<ref>{{Cite news |url=http://www.manobkantha.com/2013/07/05/128539.html |script-title=bn:\u09ed\u099f\u09bf \u099b\u09ac\u09bf \u09ae\u09c1\u0995\u09cd\u09a4\u09bf \u09aa\u09c7\u09af\u09bc\u09c7\u099b\u09bf\u09b2 |work=Manob Kantha |language=bn |access-date=26 January 2015}}</ref>\n|- \n| rowspan=5 |2007\n|  ''[[Saajghor]]'' || Shah Alam Kiron || [[Manna (actor)|Manna]], [[Moushumi]] || || '''Winner:''' Best Supporting Actress [[National Film Award (Bangladesh)|National Film Award]]\n|-\n|''Rickshawalar Prem''\n|Rokibul Alam Rokib\n|Manna\n|\n|\n|-\n|''[[Amar Praner Swami]]''\n|P A Kajal\n|Shakib Khan\n|\n|\n|-\n|''Babar Kosom''\n|Badiul Alam Khokon\n|Manna\n|\n|\n|-\n|''Meye Opohoron''\n|P A Kajal\n|[[Amin Khan (actor)|Amin Khan]]\n|\n|\n|-\n| rowspan=6 |2008\n|''Babar Jonno Judhdho''\n|[[Montazur Rahman Akbar]]\n|Manna\n|\n|\n|-\n|''Boro Bhai Zindabad''\n|Shafi Iqbal\n|Amin Khan\n|\n|\n|-\n|''Power''\n|Monowar Khokon\n|Manna\n|\n|\n|-\n|''Zamindar Barir Meye''\n|Azizur Rahman\n|Amin Khan\n|\n|\n|-\n|''Boroloker Jamai''\n|P A Kajal\n|Manna\n|\n|\n|-\n|''Koti Takar Fokir''\n|[[Abdur Razzak (actor)|Razzak]]\n|Bapparaj\n|\n|<ref>{{Cite news |url=http://www.amardeshonline.com/pages/details/2013/05/29/201961 |script-title=bn:\u09b8\u09c1\u09a8\u09bf\u